00:47:26.080 --> 00:47:30.630
Well, I thought I want to
show you a demonstration how--

00:47:30.630 --> 00:47:33.810
mechanical demonstration--
how you can sub-recoil cool.

00:47:33.810 --> 00:47:36.250
It's not a demonstration
in velocity space,

00:47:36.250 --> 00:47:38.430
it's a demonstration
in position space.

00:47:38.430 --> 00:47:40.710
What I have here
is a Plexiglas tray

00:47:40.710 --> 00:47:43.380
and it has a little
hole in the middle.

00:47:43.380 --> 00:47:45.700
And I have a bunch
of ball bearings

00:47:45.700 --> 00:47:48.332
and I put those
ball bearings in.

00:47:48.332 --> 00:47:49.040
Let me translate.

00:47:53.020 --> 00:47:58.570
I can blindfold myself and
all I do is I shake the tray.

00:47:58.570 --> 00:48:01.860
So whenever I shake
it, I kick the atoms

00:48:01.860 --> 00:48:06.570
randomly in position
space from here to here.

00:48:06.570 --> 00:48:10.420
So the amount of position
control I have over the atoms

00:48:10.420 --> 00:48:13.230
is on the order of this size.

00:48:13.230 --> 00:48:16.110
But the question is,
can I-- without having

00:48:16.110 --> 00:48:21.410
any control of the transfer
of position I give to them--

00:48:21.410 --> 00:48:24.130
can I steer all the
atoms into an area

00:48:24.130 --> 00:48:28.110
here into the hole in the
middle, which is very, very

00:48:28.110 --> 00:48:31.100
narrow in position space?

00:48:31.100 --> 00:48:34.350
So the translation is, if
I randomly scatter photons

00:48:34.350 --> 00:48:36.720
and they kick the atoms
around with h-bar K,

00:48:36.720 --> 00:48:38.710
I don't have any
control about momentum

00:48:38.710 --> 00:48:40.820
transfer smaller
than h-bar K, is it

00:48:40.820 --> 00:48:44.530
possible to localize the
atoms in momentum space

00:48:44.530 --> 00:48:46.810
to a momentum around
zero, which is

00:48:46.810 --> 00:48:49.186
much, much smaller than h-bar K?

00:48:49.186 --> 00:48:51.810
Well, let's do the experiment.

00:48:51.810 --> 00:48:56.080
I just close my eyes and I
shake it, and I shake it,

00:48:56.080 --> 00:49:01.020
and I just shake it for a while
and I continue shaking it.

00:49:01.020 --> 00:49:05.740
And, well, zero temperature!

00:49:05.740 --> 00:49:09.410
So without controlling
the motion on the scale

00:49:09.410 --> 00:49:15.950
I'm interested in, I manage to
cool into a target region which

00:49:15.950 --> 00:49:18.470
is much, much narrower.

00:49:18.470 --> 00:49:22.210
So in other words, what
you need is-- all you

00:49:22.210 --> 00:49:28.460
need is-- you need
some dark state which

00:49:28.460 --> 00:49:30.770
is velocity selective.

00:49:30.770 --> 00:49:35.240
If you scatter light but
you create a situation where

00:49:35.240 --> 00:49:41.020
once the atoms are close to zero
velocity, they're not excited.

00:49:41.020 --> 00:49:45.460
You're not steering the
atoms in a deterministic way,

00:49:45.460 --> 00:49:50.490
you just wait until-- by random
chance-- one photon is emitted,

00:49:50.490 --> 00:49:53.910
and by the random chance
the atom hits the hole.

00:49:53.910 --> 00:49:57.120
And then, it will never
be re-excited again.

00:49:57.120 --> 00:50:00.330
This was the idea of
this demonstration.

00:50:00.330 --> 00:50:04.010
And I could, yes,
in the old days

00:50:04.010 --> 00:50:06.650
I may have spent two
hours on teaching it,

00:50:06.650 --> 00:50:10.250
but by using Raman resonances
between ground states--

00:50:10.250 --> 00:50:14.740
which are terribly narrow--
or by using VSCPT-- velocity

00:50:14.740 --> 00:50:18.600
selective coherent population
trapping-- you can create

00:50:18.600 --> 00:50:21.100
such narrow dark
resonances which

00:50:21.100 --> 00:50:24.290
have the effect that the atoms
scatter, scatter, scatter,

00:50:24.290 --> 00:50:27.450
but the moment they reach a
very narrow region around zero

00:50:27.450 --> 00:50:29.840
velocity, they stop scattering.

00:50:29.840 --> 00:50:32.750
So what was wrong in my
proof is that here we

00:50:32.750 --> 00:50:38.430
have a situation where we
stop the laser cooling exactly

00:50:38.430 --> 00:50:41.220
at the time when the
atom, by random chance,

00:50:41.220 --> 00:50:45.250
happens to be at low velocity,
at very low velocity.

00:50:45.250 --> 00:50:47.250
And then you don't
need any control,

00:50:47.250 --> 00:50:49.630
you just accumulate
in the same way

00:50:49.630 --> 00:50:51.670
as I accumulated
the ball bearings.

00:51:00.130 --> 00:51:07.110
OK, this was sub-recoil cooling
in five minutes. [? Timo ?]?

00:51:07.110 --> 00:51:09.400
