00:51:26.624 --> 00:51:29.970
You could, in principle,
beat the recoil limit

00:51:29.970 --> 00:51:31.404
with Doppler cooling, no?

00:51:31.404 --> 00:51:32.850
If you have a--

00:51:32.850 --> 00:51:35.230
PROFESSOR: No, you can't,
because if you do Doppler

00:51:35.230 --> 00:51:37.430
cooling-- [? Timo's ?]
question is,

00:51:37.430 --> 00:51:42.390
if you simply do molasses
with a very, very narrow line,

00:51:42.390 --> 00:51:53.410
we derived that the limit of
Doppler cooling is Kt equals

00:51:53.410 --> 00:51:55.390
gamma, and what
you are saying now,

00:51:55.390 --> 00:51:57.740
if you use narrower
and narrower lines,

00:51:57.740 --> 00:52:00.990
can we reach [? arbitrary ?]
low temperature?

00:52:00.990 --> 00:52:02.140
This is not the case.

00:52:06.524 --> 00:52:09.340
In our derivation
of Doppler cooling,

00:52:09.340 --> 00:52:11.740
we made a continuum
assumptions when

00:52:11.740 --> 00:52:14.290
we plotted the force
versus velocity

00:52:14.290 --> 00:52:16.230
and we had the
friction force, we

00:52:16.230 --> 00:52:19.580
assumed that an atom,
when it scatters a photon,

00:52:19.580 --> 00:52:22.230
stays, let's say,
within the linear part

00:52:22.230 --> 00:52:24.500
of the force versus velocity.

00:52:24.500 --> 00:52:28.580
So we had a hidden
assumption which

00:52:28.580 --> 00:52:36.240
required that the recoil energy
is smaller than h-bar gamma.

00:52:36.240 --> 00:52:39.110
But there is a lot of literature
where people looked into it,

00:52:39.110 --> 00:52:43.040
and it turns out that when
you have a very narrow line,

00:52:43.040 --> 00:52:46.860
you can go to the recoil
limit, but you can't go beyond.

00:52:46.860 --> 00:52:49.610
If you want to go-- and I
think this is what I showed you

00:52:49.610 --> 00:52:51.570
in the last five
minutes-- if you want

00:52:51.570 --> 00:52:53.990
to go below the
recoil limit, you

00:52:53.990 --> 00:52:56.410
need some velocity-selective
dark state,

00:52:56.410 --> 00:53:00.620
and you would not have
that in this situation.

00:53:00.620 --> 00:53:03.490
On the other hand, if you
have a very narrow resonance,

00:53:03.490 --> 00:53:05.993
you can probably
engineer a dark state

00:53:05.993 --> 00:53:09.830
that there is destructive
interference in some excitation

00:53:09.830 --> 00:53:12.140
in a very, very
narrow velocity class,

00:53:12.140 --> 00:53:14.050
and this narrow
velocity class is simply

00:53:14.050 --> 00:53:17.160
selected by the Doppler effect.

00:53:17.160 --> 00:53:25.420
So you can use the narrow line
to engineer sub-recoil cooling,

00:53:25.420 --> 00:53:27.690
but the simple arrangement
of just having molasses

00:53:27.690 --> 00:53:30.290
with narrower and narrower
line will not work.

