00:54:23.980 --> 00:54:24.605
Other question?

00:54:31.040 --> 00:54:36.320
OK, so I've told you
about sub-Doppler cooling,

00:54:36.320 --> 00:54:40.525
sub-recoil cooling, but what
really got atomic physicists

00:54:40.525 --> 00:54:43.900
to nanokelvin temperature
were two other techniques.

00:54:43.900 --> 00:54:47.620
Laser cooling was
used as pre-cooling,

00:54:47.620 --> 00:54:50.070
but then the final
trapping and cooling

00:54:50.070 --> 00:54:53.880
was done by magnetic trapping
and evaporative cooling.

00:54:53.880 --> 00:54:56.840
So I want to give you
now, in the last half

00:54:56.840 --> 00:55:01.860
hour, a quick overview
of magnetic trapping

00:55:01.860 --> 00:55:04.590
and evaporative cooling.

00:55:04.590 --> 00:55:10.240
So I think any discussions
of magnetic trapping starts

00:55:10.240 --> 00:55:14.400
with a theorem, a
theorem which tells you

00:55:14.400 --> 00:55:16.980
that not everything is
possible you would like to do.

00:55:16.980 --> 00:55:22.420
And this is the following, then
if you have a region without

00:55:22.420 --> 00:55:26.260
charges and currents without--
through an empty space,

00:55:26.260 --> 00:55:30.930
and what this theorem
says-- in empty space,

00:55:30.930 --> 00:55:35.780
you cannot have
a local minimum--

00:55:35.780 --> 00:55:38.530
you cannot have a local maximum
of your electric and magnetic

00:55:38.530 --> 00:55:39.330
fields.

00:55:39.330 --> 00:55:42.010
So if you take the strengths
of the electric field

00:55:42.010 --> 00:55:43.950
or the strengths of
the magnetic field,

00:55:43.950 --> 00:55:45.404
you cannot have a maximum.

00:55:45.404 --> 00:55:46.570
You can only have a minimum.

00:55:49.080 --> 00:55:52.520
Well, and this is important
when it comes to magnetic traps.

00:55:52.520 --> 00:55:55.830
Depending on the magnetic
moment-- spin up,

00:55:55.830 --> 00:55:59.620
spin down-- we could
create a trapping potential

00:55:59.620 --> 00:56:02.480
around a maximum of
the magnetic field

00:56:02.480 --> 00:56:04.560
or the trapping potential
around the minimum

00:56:04.560 --> 00:56:05.890
of the magnetic field.

00:56:05.890 --> 00:56:08.865
You want to be at the
minimum of the potential,

00:56:08.865 --> 00:56:10.240
but if you have
a minus sign, you

00:56:10.240 --> 00:56:13.020
may want to be at the
maximum of a magnetic field.

00:56:13.020 --> 00:56:15.790
But [? Bing's ?] theorem
says that only one of them

00:56:15.790 --> 00:56:18.000
is possible.

00:56:18.000 --> 00:56:21.180
The proof really
goes in two lines.

00:56:21.180 --> 00:56:25.610
You really show, if you assume
that there is a maximum, that

00:56:25.610 --> 00:56:31.590
would mean that if you add a
field to it, you add a field--

00:56:31.590 --> 00:56:34.620
and no matter in which
direction you add a field--

00:56:34.620 --> 00:56:36.425
the total field
strengths become smaller.

00:56:40.600 --> 00:56:44.515
But that requires a violation
of the Laplace equation.

00:56:47.660 --> 00:56:50.310
It's easier for you-- you can
probably read it at home--

00:56:50.310 --> 00:56:53.370
but you simply assume
you have this situation,

00:56:53.370 --> 00:56:56.280
so you add-- and you show you
have an incremental field,

00:56:56.280 --> 00:56:59.360
delta E. This
field, delta E, you

00:56:59.360 --> 00:57:01.710
are at the maximum
of an electric field,

00:57:01.710 --> 00:57:04.440
and then delta E over R
is the small difference

00:57:04.440 --> 00:57:05.930
of the electric field.

00:57:05.930 --> 00:57:12.140
And you can show that this
expression is only negative.

00:57:12.140 --> 00:57:18.750
That means you have a maximum
of the electric field when

00:57:18.750 --> 00:57:24.060
the electric field would not
fulfill the Laplace equation.

00:57:24.060 --> 00:57:26.920
So the gist of the
argument is the following.

00:57:26.920 --> 00:57:29.290
Each component of the
electric and magnetic field

00:57:29.290 --> 00:57:31.140
fulfills the Laplace equation.

00:57:31.140 --> 00:57:34.060
And the Laplace equation-- I
don't know if you've probably

00:57:34.060 --> 00:57:37.020
heard about it-- if something
fulfills the Laplace equation,

00:57:37.020 --> 00:57:40.630
it says at any given
point the function which

00:57:40.630 --> 00:57:44.190
fulfills the Laplace equation
is equal to the average

00:57:44.190 --> 00:57:49.190
of function, averaged over
a small sphere around it.

00:57:49.190 --> 00:57:54.860
And that means-- if something
fulfills the Laplace equation--

00:57:54.860 --> 00:57:57.440
you cannot have a local
maximum or a local minimum

00:57:57.440 --> 00:58:00.810
because if the value
here equals the average,

00:58:00.810 --> 00:58:06.080
that would mean in one
direction the value gets higher,

00:58:06.080 --> 00:58:08.800
in the other direction
the value gets lower.

00:58:08.800 --> 00:58:11.870
So if something fulfills
the Laplace equation,

00:58:11.870 --> 00:58:15.150
you cannot have a local
maximum or local minimum.

00:58:15.150 --> 00:58:19.060
But now, we're not asking
for maximum or minimum

00:58:19.060 --> 00:58:22.380
in one component of the
electric or magnetic field.

00:58:22.380 --> 00:58:26.860
We ask for a maximum or
minimum in the total value,

00:58:26.860 --> 00:58:29.540
or the square of
the electric field.

00:58:29.540 --> 00:58:32.900
But then you show, when you
assume that you have a maximum,

00:58:32.900 --> 00:58:35.290
the field points
along the Z direction,

00:58:35.290 --> 00:58:39.640
that then the Z component
of the field cannot fulfill

00:58:39.640 --> 00:58:42.480
the Laplace equation.

00:58:42.480 --> 00:58:45.090
So maxima are not possible.

00:58:45.090 --> 00:58:48.640
Minima are possible.

00:58:48.640 --> 00:58:49.350
Good!

00:58:49.350 --> 00:58:51.320
So the magnetic
trapping potential

00:58:51.320 --> 00:58:54.530
comes because we have a
magnetic dipole moment which

00:58:54.530 --> 00:58:57.620
interacts with a magnetic field.

00:58:57.620 --> 00:59:00.220
Magnetic traps are
actually classical.

00:59:00.220 --> 00:59:03.200
You can have a classical
model for a magnetic trap,

00:59:03.200 --> 00:59:06.220
and in that case, you
say this potentially

00:59:06.220 --> 00:59:08.760
is mu times B
times cosine theta.

00:59:08.760 --> 00:59:11.840
[? Crendo ?] mechanically, of
course, the angle cosine theta

00:59:11.840 --> 00:59:15.580
is quantized and we have
the different M F levels,

00:59:15.580 --> 00:59:17.950
the different
orientations of the spin,

00:59:17.950 --> 00:59:18.910
relative to the Z-axis.

00:59:21.740 --> 00:59:26.790
OK, the fact that the
magnetic field can only

00:59:26.790 --> 00:59:32.070
have minima and not
maxima means that we

00:59:32.070 --> 00:59:36.120
want to make sure that the
magnetic moment times the G

00:59:36.120 --> 00:59:39.750
factor times M F is
negative, or cosine theta

00:59:39.750 --> 00:59:42.960
is negative in the
classical picture.

00:59:42.960 --> 00:59:46.930
And if we absorb whatever
we choose for cosine theta--

00:59:46.930 --> 00:59:51.320
or what we call mu Bohr G
M F, the magnetic moment--

00:59:51.320 --> 00:59:54.360
we want that the magnetic
moment of the particle

00:59:54.360 --> 01:00:00.490
is anti-parallel to
the magnetic field.

01:00:00.490 --> 01:00:02.750
Then we have a magnetic
trapping potential,

01:00:02.750 --> 01:00:06.750
which is-- I've taken care
of the sin now-- mu times B,

01:00:06.750 --> 01:00:10.250
and if B has a minimum this
potential has a minimum,

01:00:10.250 --> 01:00:13.190
and that is a magnetic trap.

01:00:13.190 --> 01:00:15.990
But so the consequence
of [? Bing's ?] theorem

01:00:15.990 --> 01:00:20.430
is that we can
only trap particles

01:00:20.430 --> 01:00:24.960
which are anti-parallel
with a magnetic field.

01:00:24.960 --> 01:00:27.840
And they can always
lower their energy

01:00:27.840 --> 01:00:31.030
by flipping to the other state.

01:00:31.030 --> 01:00:34.150
So therefore, a
magnetic trap does not

01:00:34.150 --> 01:00:37.966
allow us to trap particles
in the absolute ground state.

01:00:37.966 --> 01:00:41.810
There is always the possibility
of spin-flip collisions

01:00:41.810 --> 01:00:44.730
which lead to an
anti-trap state which

01:00:44.730 --> 01:00:46.470
is expelled from
the trapping region.

01:00:50.370 --> 01:00:52.990
Now, spin-flip
collisions can happen

01:00:52.990 --> 01:00:55.610
when you have particles at
sufficiently high density

01:00:55.610 --> 01:00:58.560
and they collide.

01:00:58.560 --> 01:01:02.860
For the experts, there
can be spin relaxation,

01:01:02.860 --> 01:01:04.620
there can be dipolar
relaxation, they

01:01:04.620 --> 01:01:07.050
are two different kinds
of spin-flip collisions.

01:01:07.050 --> 01:01:11.180
Fortunately, in magnetic
traps, they only

01:01:11.180 --> 01:01:14.980
become relevant when you
pick the wrong spin state.

01:01:14.980 --> 01:01:18.650
But for suitable
choices, magnetic traps

01:01:18.650 --> 01:01:21.160
are very long-lived.

01:01:21.160 --> 01:01:26.120
Dipolar relaxation is often--
can be a limiting process

01:01:26.120 --> 01:01:28.130
for Bose-Einstein
condensates, for instance,

01:01:28.130 --> 01:01:30.200
for high [? dose ?]
Bose-Einstein condensation,

01:01:30.200 --> 01:01:35.530
dipolar relaxation was-- limited
the number and density of atoms

01:01:35.530 --> 01:01:37.410
in the Bose-Einstein condensate.

01:01:37.410 --> 01:01:40.080
But I don't want to talk
about cold collisions, here.

01:01:40.080 --> 01:01:43.660
You should just know, based
on the fundamental theorem,

01:01:43.660 --> 01:01:45.440
you cannot trap in
the ground state.

01:01:45.440 --> 01:01:48.410
You have to trap
into a state which

01:01:48.410 --> 01:01:51.590
has more energy than other
states, and, in principle,

01:01:51.590 --> 01:02:00.860
it's possible to flip the
spin and go to a lower state.

01:02:00.860 --> 01:02:04.400
Now, what we have
assumed here is--

01:02:04.400 --> 01:02:06.600
when I wrote the trapping
potential like this--

01:02:06.600 --> 01:02:10.320
I assumed that the atom stays
in a given hyperfine state.

01:02:10.320 --> 01:02:15.050
So we put the atom in one state
and it experiences potential.

01:02:15.050 --> 01:02:18.590
Classically it means that
the angle of the dipole,

01:02:18.590 --> 01:02:22.160
with respect to the magnetic
field, stays constant.

01:02:22.160 --> 01:02:25.070
And this is the case
due to rapid precession.

01:02:25.070 --> 01:02:27.870
Classically, the
magnetic dipole precesses

01:02:27.870 --> 01:02:29.870
around the magnetic
field, and when

01:02:29.870 --> 01:02:32.530
the direction of the
magnetic field changes,

01:02:32.530 --> 01:02:36.390
the rapid precession
keeps the dipole aligned.

01:02:36.390 --> 01:02:40.320
Or, in other words, for slow
changes of the magnetic field

01:02:40.320 --> 01:02:46.300
direction, cosine theta
is an adiabatic invariant.

01:02:46.300 --> 01:02:49.660
So the word adiabatic is
important, either classically

01:02:49.660 --> 01:02:52.780
or you stay in a quantum state
as long as you're adiabatic.

01:02:55.370 --> 01:03:00.150
Well if an atom would
rapidly go through a region

01:03:00.150 --> 01:03:03.870
of very weak magnetic
field, then the precession--

01:03:03.870 --> 01:03:06.190
the [INAUDIBLE] precession--
of the atom is very slow,

01:03:06.190 --> 01:03:10.210
and this adiabatic
condition can be violated.

01:03:10.210 --> 01:03:13.610
And this violation of an
adiabaticity condition

01:03:13.610 --> 01:03:16.840
is called Majorana flops.

01:03:16.840 --> 01:03:19.100
So if you operate
a magnetic trap

01:03:19.100 --> 01:03:23.145
at very low magnetic field,
you may destabilized the trap

01:03:23.145 --> 01:03:24.520
because you violate
adiabaticity.

01:03:27.780 --> 01:03:30.850
OK, so these are the
consequences of the fact that

01:03:30.850 --> 01:03:34.260
we cannot create maxima,
we can only create minima

01:03:34.260 --> 01:03:36.410
of the magnetic
field in free space,

01:03:36.410 --> 01:03:40.690
and therefore we have to deal
with those two possible loss

01:03:40.690 --> 01:03:46.380
processes, but we have learned
what kind of magnetic trap,

01:03:46.380 --> 01:03:49.870
what kind of atom to pick, and
in general these are not big

01:03:49.870 --> 01:03:52.370
problems.

01:03:52.370 --> 01:03:56.810
OK, so we have to--
so this shows here

01:03:56.810 --> 01:03:59.520
the typical hyperfine
structure of an alkali atom.

01:03:59.520 --> 01:04:04.450
It could be rubidium
87 or sodium 23.

01:04:04.450 --> 01:04:07.740
The fact that we have
only a local minimum

01:04:07.740 --> 01:04:15.090
of the magnetic field means
we can only trap hyperfine

01:04:15.090 --> 01:04:19.010
states-- which I've marked here
in green-- where the slope is

01:04:19.010 --> 01:04:21.760
positive, and these
are the atoms where

01:04:21.760 --> 01:04:23.630
the magnetic moment
is inter-parallel

01:04:23.630 --> 01:04:26.800
with the magnetic field.

01:04:26.800 --> 01:04:29.920
And, well, for
stability reasons we

01:04:29.920 --> 01:04:33.440
usually pick the highest
state of the lower manifold,

01:04:33.440 --> 01:04:35.900
or the highest state
of the upper manifold.

01:04:35.900 --> 01:04:38.370
In principle, it would
be also possible to trap

01:04:38.370 --> 01:04:41.670
here-- you have
the correct slope--

01:04:41.670 --> 01:04:44.960
but often those
states suffer form

01:04:44.960 --> 01:04:47.320
spin relaxation
and collision loss.

01:04:49.629 --> 01:04:50.170
[? Mickey ?]?

01:04:50.170 --> 01:04:53.520
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE] the
picture you showed before,

01:04:53.520 --> 01:04:57.790
is it actually possible to
make a magnetic trap with state

01:04:57.790 --> 01:05:03.225
number four from the top so
that they expel from the center?

01:05:03.225 --> 01:05:05.660
From [INAUDIBLE] a--

01:05:05.660 --> 01:05:08.000
PROFESSOR: Yeah, there
is a peculiarity here,

01:05:08.000 --> 01:05:12.220
you have the transition from the
weak field to the strong field

01:05:12.220 --> 01:05:13.430
region.

01:05:13.430 --> 01:05:16.630
Whenever the magnetic
moment is constant,

01:05:16.630 --> 01:05:19.960
you need a local minimum
of the magnetic field.

01:05:19.960 --> 01:05:23.750
But if the magnetic
moment would change

01:05:23.750 --> 01:05:26.680
and you have a gradient
of the magnetic field,

01:05:26.680 --> 01:05:29.630
you could actually trap here.

01:05:29.630 --> 01:05:35.060
So in this case, you have
a magnetic field gradient

01:05:35.060 --> 01:05:39.240
but you have a spatial variation
of the magnetic moment.

01:05:39.240 --> 01:05:41.730
This has been discussed
in one special paper

01:05:41.730 --> 01:05:43.690
in the literature,
but it has not really

01:05:43.690 --> 01:05:45.862
found any [? lucent ?]
realization.

01:05:45.862 --> 01:05:48.222
AUDIENCE: Wouldn't it
help to put the Majorana

01:05:48.222 --> 01:05:49.638
flops in the center?

01:05:49.638 --> 01:05:51.580
Because they're repelled
from the center.

01:05:51.580 --> 01:05:54.290
PROFESSOR: Well,
yeah, but these atoms

01:05:54.290 --> 01:05:55.910
would undergo
spin-flip collisions

01:05:55.910 --> 01:05:59.090
so it's not a good choice.

01:05:59.090 --> 01:06:00.920
It would help against
Majorana flops,

01:06:00.920 --> 01:06:04.550
but we have many solutions
against Majorana flops.

01:06:04.550 --> 01:06:07.360
And here, you would solve
the Majorana flops problem

01:06:07.360 --> 01:06:10.930
but you would solve it
with another problem.

01:06:10.930 --> 01:06:14.660
OK, so we need minima
of the magnetic field.

01:06:14.660 --> 01:06:19.230
This provides magnetic
trapping potential,

01:06:19.230 --> 01:06:24.680
and there are two kinds of
possible trap configuration.

01:06:24.680 --> 01:06:29.470
One is where the minima
is at zero magnetic field,

01:06:29.470 --> 01:06:33.480
and one is where the minima
is at finite magnetic field.

01:06:33.480 --> 01:06:36.400
Now, the zero magnetic
field minimum one

01:06:36.400 --> 01:06:40.850
can be simply created
with anti-Helmholtz coil.

01:06:40.850 --> 01:06:44.590
What happens is
the magnetic field,

01:06:44.590 --> 01:06:49.210
as a function of position, would
actually cross through zero.

01:06:49.210 --> 01:06:52.620
It's just a field gradient
which crosses through zero,

01:06:52.620 --> 01:06:55.227
but, of course, since
we are interested

01:06:55.227 --> 01:06:57.060
in the absolute value
of the magnetic field,

01:06:57.060 --> 01:07:00.420
we get the V-shape potential.

01:07:00.420 --> 01:07:03.020
This V-shape
potential was what was

01:07:03.020 --> 01:07:06.620
used for the first demonstration
for Bose-Einstein condensation

01:07:06.620 --> 01:07:10.650
because a V-shape potential
is much, much more

01:07:10.650 --> 01:07:15.050
confining in this cusp than in
harmonic oscillator potential.

01:07:15.050 --> 01:07:18.240
And this had advantages
for tight confinement

01:07:18.240 --> 01:07:20.520
and rapid evaporative cooling.

01:07:20.520 --> 01:07:23.875
So those quadrupoled traps
with the V-shape potential

01:07:23.875 --> 01:07:27.380
are the best
confinement you can get,

01:07:27.380 --> 01:07:29.190
the best confinement
for the buck,

01:07:29.190 --> 01:07:33.720
and the buck here is your
power supply and your coils.

01:07:33.720 --> 01:07:36.020
However, they have
a problem when

01:07:36.020 --> 01:07:37.990
the magnetic field is zero.

01:07:37.990 --> 01:07:42.050
We violate adiabaticity
because the different spin

01:07:42.050 --> 01:07:44.210
configurations
become degenerate,

01:07:44.210 --> 01:07:47.610
and in degenerates you
can't have adiabaticity.

01:07:47.610 --> 01:07:49.800
So therefore, the two
first demonstrations

01:07:49.800 --> 01:07:53.620
of Bose-Einstein condensation
avoided this cusp

01:07:53.620 --> 01:07:55.510
in two different ways.

01:07:55.510 --> 01:08:00.560
One way was to use a
rotating magnetic field,

01:08:00.560 --> 01:08:04.410
and to use a perpendicular field
but which was time-dependent,

01:08:04.410 --> 01:08:08.330
and the MIT solution was to
use a blue detuned laser beam,

01:08:08.330 --> 01:08:11.870
use the optical dipole trap--
optical dipole potential--

01:08:11.870 --> 01:08:16.050
to push the atoms away from
the dangerous [INAUDIBLE]

01:08:16.050 --> 01:08:18.100
field region.

01:08:18.100 --> 01:08:25.540
I should say rotating-- none
of those-- most traps which

01:08:25.540 --> 01:08:29.080
are now used are the other
kind of trap, the trap which

01:08:29.080 --> 01:08:34.649
has an harmonic oscillator
potential, which doesn't have

01:08:34.649 --> 01:08:40.569
the cusp and where the minimum
is at a finite magnetic field.

01:08:40.569 --> 01:08:42.569
Let me just make one comment.

01:08:42.569 --> 01:08:44.500
The rotating trap
was very popular

01:08:44.500 --> 01:08:47.859
because it led to the first BEC
and a lot of people built that,

01:08:47.859 --> 01:08:49.770
but to the best of
my knowledge, it's

01:08:49.770 --> 01:08:53.060
only used in different places.

01:08:53.060 --> 01:08:57.880
And the only real
application it has

01:08:57.880 --> 01:09:02.340
is-- since you have some
rotating magnetic field--

01:09:02.340 --> 01:09:04.790
by some modification
you can actually

01:09:04.790 --> 01:09:06.970
make of rotating potential.

01:09:06.970 --> 01:09:08.859
And this is nice if
you want to study

01:09:08.859 --> 01:09:11.410
Bose-Einstein condensation
on a rotating frame,

01:09:11.410 --> 01:09:14.800
create vortices and
things like that.

01:09:14.800 --> 01:09:17.790
But for simply creating a
Bose-Einstein condensate,

01:09:17.790 --> 01:09:21.740
this trap is used, by
far, most frequently.

01:09:21.740 --> 01:09:25.540
But there is actually a
renaissance of this trap.

01:09:25.540 --> 01:09:27.149
One reason why
people use this trap

01:09:27.149 --> 01:09:29.859
and why my own research
group immediately

01:09:29.859 --> 01:09:31.330
switched to this
trap-- and we had

01:09:31.330 --> 01:09:34.260
the idea how to built it--
is, well, harmonic potential

01:09:34.260 --> 01:09:34.760
is nice.

01:09:34.760 --> 01:09:37.029
Every physicist loves
an harmonic potential.

01:09:37.029 --> 01:09:39.490
You can solve,
immediately, thermodynamics

01:09:39.490 --> 01:09:40.880
in a harmonic potential.

01:09:40.880 --> 01:09:43.630
Who wants to deal
with that potential?

01:09:43.630 --> 01:09:46.420
Also, if the laser beam
just drifts by a micrometer,

01:09:46.420 --> 01:09:49.750
this symmetric potential
becomes asymmetric.

01:09:49.750 --> 01:09:51.970
So you characterize
your potential today

01:09:51.970 --> 01:09:54.450
and a few hours later you
have a different potential.

01:09:54.450 --> 01:09:57.140
Whereas a magnetic potential,
harmonic potential,

01:09:57.140 --> 01:09:59.880
once it's characterized--
as long as you don't change

01:09:59.880 --> 01:10:01.480
the current in your
power supplies--

01:10:01.480 --> 01:10:04.550
it's the same week after
week, months after months.

01:10:04.550 --> 01:10:08.430
Well, there is a renaissance
now because a lot of groups

01:10:08.430 --> 01:10:10.520
now doing experiments
in optical lattices,

01:10:10.520 --> 01:10:14.430
they don't care what shape the
potential is because they don't

01:10:14.430 --> 01:10:16.210
do physics in this potential.

01:10:16.210 --> 01:10:19.010
They just take the Bose-Einstein
condensate or the cooled Fermi

01:10:19.010 --> 01:10:22.220
gases and transfer them
to an optical lattice.

01:10:22.220 --> 01:10:24.960
So in that case, it
doesn't play any role,

01:10:24.960 --> 01:10:26.940
and then the advantage
of this potential

01:10:26.940 --> 01:10:30.147
is you get more
bang for the buck.

01:10:30.147 --> 01:10:35.636
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE] you were
saying before [INAUDIBLE] more

01:10:35.636 --> 01:10:38.640
rapid evaporation in V-shape
versus the [INAUDIBLE].

01:10:38.640 --> 01:10:43.840
Where is the differences
in evap time?

01:10:43.840 --> 01:10:46.390
PROFESSOR: It depends.

01:10:46.390 --> 01:10:47.930
I may run out of time today.

01:10:47.930 --> 01:10:50.700
I needed-- I can
probably-- I wanted

01:10:50.700 --> 01:10:52.300
to go through
evaporative cooling,

01:10:52.300 --> 01:10:55.230
and I will talk to you that,
for evaporative cooling,

01:10:55.230 --> 01:10:57.520
there could be a
threshold in confinement

01:10:57.520 --> 01:10:59.680
where you go into
a runaway regime

01:10:59.680 --> 01:11:02.250
that evaporative
cooling is speeding up.

01:11:02.250 --> 01:11:08.650
So a little bit of confinement
can make the difference

01:11:08.650 --> 01:11:11.240
without never getting
into a runaway regime

01:11:11.240 --> 01:11:12.940
or being in that runaway regime.

01:11:12.940 --> 01:11:14.900
So confinement,
extra confinement,

01:11:14.900 --> 01:11:17.340
can make the difference
between getting BEC and not

01:11:17.340 --> 01:11:20.230
getting a BEC.

01:11:20.230 --> 01:11:21.220
So it really depends.

01:11:21.220 --> 01:11:23.630
It's highly nonlinear,
but I will show you

01:11:23.630 --> 01:11:28.200
later on that when you
put a system together,

01:11:28.200 --> 01:11:31.700
the kind of threshold density
at which the cloud can evaporate

01:11:31.700 --> 01:11:34.745
to BEC is much lower
here than it is there.

01:11:38.140 --> 01:11:39.780
But-- and this is
the next thing I

01:11:39.780 --> 01:11:41.540
want to explain--
it's not really

01:11:41.540 --> 01:11:43.960
that this is a linear potential
and this is a [INAUDIBLE]

01:11:43.960 --> 01:11:49.380
potential because those
finite magnetic field--

01:11:49.380 --> 01:11:52.540
these traps which have a minimum
at a finite magnetic field--

01:11:52.540 --> 01:11:56.510
are usually done in
the following way.

01:11:56.510 --> 01:11:59.940
Those traps are called
Ioffe-Pritchard trap.

01:11:59.940 --> 01:12:04.330
Ioffe actually suggested such
a magnetic field configuration

01:12:04.330 --> 01:12:07.530
for confinement of
plasma, and Dave Pritchard

01:12:07.530 --> 01:12:10.670
was the first to point out
that such a configuration would

01:12:10.670 --> 01:12:13.460
be a good choice
for neutral atoms.

01:12:13.460 --> 01:12:16.730
So I sometimes joke and I
say, well, plasma physics

01:12:16.730 --> 01:12:18.800
is the study of very hot matter.

01:12:18.800 --> 01:12:21.540
Cold atoms is the study
of very cold matter.

01:12:21.540 --> 01:12:25.520
But when matter is either too
hot or too cold that you cannot

01:12:25.520 --> 01:12:28.440
put it in ordinary container,
you want it confined with

01:12:28.440 --> 01:12:29.750
magnetic fields.

01:12:29.750 --> 01:12:32.030
And it happens that,
for plasma, you

01:12:32.030 --> 01:12:35.690
need a minimum of the magnetic
field, and for neutral atoms

01:12:35.690 --> 01:12:37.710
you need a minimum of
the magnetic field.

01:12:37.710 --> 01:12:40.960
So therefore here is something
which ultra-cold atoms have

01:12:40.960 --> 01:12:43.432
in common with plasma physics.

01:12:43.432 --> 01:12:45.890
I don't think there is a lot
the two fields have in common,

01:12:45.890 --> 01:12:49.450
but when it comes to magnetic
field configurations, yes.

01:12:49.450 --> 01:12:53.760
A similar magnetic
field configuration

01:12:53.760 --> 01:12:59.230
can confine a plasma and
can confine neutral atoms.

01:12:59.230 --> 01:13:05.480
OK, so the generic way of
how these magnetic fields are

01:13:05.480 --> 01:13:14.720
generated is you want to have
two coils, called pinch coils.

01:13:14.720 --> 01:13:18.230
You can say each of them creates
a magnetic field which decays,

01:13:18.230 --> 01:13:20.570
a magnetic field which
decays, and now in the middle

01:13:20.570 --> 01:13:23.370
you have the parabolic minimum.

01:13:23.370 --> 01:13:27.800
But then you have to add the
so-called four Ioffe bars which

01:13:27.800 --> 01:13:30.520
create a linear potential,
and this is shown here.

01:13:30.520 --> 01:13:33.640
So the pinch coil is simply
creating a local minimum

01:13:33.640 --> 01:13:36.270
along the Z-axis,
and if you only

01:13:36.270 --> 01:13:38.780
want to trap in one
dimension, you would be done,

01:13:38.780 --> 01:13:41.060
But you want to trap
in 3 dimensions.

01:13:41.060 --> 01:13:43.532
And so what happens
is you add now

01:13:43.532 --> 01:13:47.940
an anti-Helmholtz-- or
quadrupold-- field in X and Y,

01:13:47.940 --> 01:13:52.260
and this blue field is
done via the green bars,

01:13:52.260 --> 01:13:53.650
by the Ioffe bars.

01:13:53.650 --> 01:13:58.150
So you add together a harmonic
quadratic field in the Z

01:13:58.150 --> 01:14:03.000
direction with the linear
quadrupoled field in X and Y.

01:14:03.000 --> 01:14:05.530
And what matters
for the atoms is--

01:14:05.530 --> 01:14:07.580
and what matters for
the Zeeman energy

01:14:07.580 --> 01:14:11.060
is-- the absolute value
of the magnetic field.

01:14:11.060 --> 01:14:13.380
So you add those
things in quadrature,

01:14:13.380 --> 01:14:15.430
and because you add
it in quadrature,

01:14:15.430 --> 01:14:18.380
you have now an harmonic
oscillator potential

01:14:18.380 --> 01:14:21.100
in X, Y, and Z, so
you have an harmonic

01:14:21.100 --> 01:14:24.830
trap in three directions.

01:14:24.830 --> 01:14:30.510
However, if this field
is not larger than this--

01:14:30.510 --> 01:14:33.350
if these field becomes
larger than this field,

01:14:33.350 --> 01:14:35.250
so then when you add
it in quadrature,

01:14:35.250 --> 01:14:38.150
you actually get a
linear potential.

01:14:38.150 --> 01:14:40.950
So in other words, the
Ioffe-Pritchard trap

01:14:40.950 --> 01:14:44.580
is quadratic for smaller
values of X and Y,

01:14:44.580 --> 01:14:47.170
but if you go out
to large X and Y,

01:14:47.170 --> 01:14:49.330
you get the linear potential.

01:14:49.330 --> 01:14:51.980
So in the end-- and this
is maybe in response

01:14:51.980 --> 01:14:56.080
to Matt's question--
for a high temperature,

01:14:56.080 --> 01:14:58.160
the Ioffe-Pritchard
trap is actually not

01:14:58.160 --> 01:14:59.880
harmonic in three dimensions.

01:14:59.880 --> 01:15:01.640
It's linear in
two dimensions and

01:15:01.640 --> 01:15:03.960
harmonic in the third dimension.

01:15:03.960 --> 01:15:07.480
So, therefore the hit you
take in evaporative cooling

01:15:07.480 --> 01:15:11.430
is not as large as
we'd initially assumed.

01:15:11.430 --> 01:15:14.500
And the moment we
realized that, we

01:15:14.500 --> 01:15:17.750
were building a
Ioffe-Pritchard trap.

01:15:17.750 --> 01:15:19.620
And this has been
the traps we' have

01:15:19.620 --> 01:15:23.340
been using at MIT ever since.

01:15:23.340 --> 01:15:27.300
Well, just as a warning, this
is sort of the simplified

01:15:27.300 --> 01:15:30.110
description, but if
you have curvature,

01:15:30.110 --> 01:15:33.100
the curvature has to
fulfill Maxwell's equation.

01:15:33.100 --> 01:15:36.290
And you cannot have a
curvature only along Z.

01:15:36.290 --> 01:15:38.710
Maxwell's equations
are three-dimensional,

01:15:38.710 --> 01:15:41.500
so you get sort of all
sorts of curvature terms.

01:15:41.500 --> 01:15:43.640
If you really build
a magnetic trap,

01:15:43.640 --> 01:15:45.160
you should understand those.

01:15:45.160 --> 01:15:47.895
If you just want to understand
why magnetic traps work,

01:15:47.895 --> 01:15:49.270
the previous slide
is sufficient.

01:15:51.930 --> 01:15:54.860
The different ways
to build those traps,

01:15:54.860 --> 01:15:57.370
this is the design
we invented at MIT.

01:15:57.370 --> 01:15:59.410
It's called a clover-leaf trap.

01:15:59.410 --> 01:16:05.800
So you have one
coil package here,

01:16:05.800 --> 01:16:08.110
to another coil
package here, and what

01:16:08.110 --> 01:16:11.360
you see is the pinch coils,
and when you have two of them

01:16:11.360 --> 01:16:15.350
you create this
parabolic minimum.

01:16:15.350 --> 01:16:19.170
We don't like Ioffe bars because
if you have a vacuum chamber

01:16:19.170 --> 01:16:21.670
you either have to put the Ioffe
bars into the vector vacuum

01:16:21.670 --> 01:16:24.030
chamber or you drill holes
through your vacuum chamber

01:16:24.030 --> 01:16:26.127
to put the Ioffe
bars back and forth.

01:16:26.127 --> 01:16:27.710
Don't laugh, some
people have done it.

01:16:27.710 --> 01:16:29.459
Of course, they put
little tubes around it

01:16:29.459 --> 01:16:31.520
so it was a very
highly-engineered vacuum

01:16:31.520 --> 01:16:34.740
chamber where they could string
Ioffe bars through the chamber.

01:16:34.740 --> 01:16:37.880
But we realized that the
same field as Ioffe bars

01:16:37.880 --> 01:16:41.600
can be generated by
taking the Ioffe bars

01:16:41.600 --> 01:16:45.500
and flipping them out, and
after flipping them out,

01:16:45.500 --> 01:16:47.590
they had the shape
of clover leaves.

01:16:47.590 --> 01:16:53.010
It's just a variant of creating
the same field geometry.

